Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Standalone Personal Emergency Response Systems Market

Standalone personal emergency response systems market is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate of 14.10% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on standalone personal emergency response systems provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecasted period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth.

The personal emergency response systems are devices which are particularly designed so that one can get instantaneous support during any urgent situation. They generally consist of three main components such as small radio transmitter, console which is linked to telephone and an emergency response centre which back calls.

The presence of a large number of geriatric populations across the world have been directly influencing the growth of standalone personal emergency response systems market over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Also the rising number of dependents, mainly the disabled and elderly, who need better care and attention for health, is raising the need for flexible mode of notification systems and is also flourishing the growth of the standalone personal emergency response systems market. Also the increasing prevalence of chronic diseases amongst people around the globe is also positively impacting the growth of the market. Furthermore, the rising involvement of smartphones in healthcare industry and growing life expectancy are also acting as an active growth driver towards the growth of the standalone personal emergency response systems market. Moreover, the rising trend of independent living across the globe has encouraged the high adoption of personal emergency response systems which is creating a huge demand for standalone personal emergency response systems as well as lifting the growth of the standalone personal emergency response systems market. However, the lack of knowledge regarding the technologies used in personal emergency response systems as well as the less adequacy of the technology in low and middle-income nations are acting as the major limitations for the growth of standalone personal emergency response systems in the above mentioned forecasted period, whereas the high cost coupled with the manufacturing of personal emergency response systems have the potential to challenge the standalone personal emergency response systems market growth in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

Likewise, the rising investments of government to develop healthcare infrastructure and growing focus on R&D activities will further cater ample new opportunities that will lead to the growth of the standalone personal emergency response systems market in the above mentioned forecasted period.

